                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      , Acute sinusitis                                                                                                                                                                  , "S pneumoniae H influenzae Moraxella catarrhalis"                                                                                                                                                                                     , "Amoxicillin OR Amoxicillin- clavulanate (Allergyb: Clindamycin OR Levofloxacin)"                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           , 5-7 days                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  , "Diagnosis of acute bacterial sinusitis requires the presence of one of the following criteria: (1) persistent nasal discharge or daytime cough without evidence of clinical improvement for $\ge10$ days; consider watchful waiting in this scenario (2) worsening or new onset of nasal discharge, daytime cough, or fever after initial improvement (3) temperature $\ge39^{\circ}C$ with purulent nasal discharge and/ or facial pain for at least 3 consecutive days"                                                                                                                                          , "Haemophilus influenzae Infections, p 400 Moraxella catarrhalis Infections, p 604 Streptococcus pneumoniae (P