                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      , Acute otitis media                                                                                                                                                               , "Spneumoniae H influenzae M catarrhalis"                                                                                                                                                                                              , "Amoxicillin OR Amoxicillin- clavulanate (Allergy: Cefdinir OR Cefpodoxime OR Cefuroxime OR Ceftriaxone for 1 (first occurrence) to 3 (treatment failure) days"                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             , ">6 y: 5 days 2-5 y: 7 days <2 y or severe symptoms: 10 days"                                                                                                                                                                             , "Consider observation without antibiotics for 48-72 hours for children 24 months or older without severe symptoms; if symptoms persist or worsen, use same antibiotic recommendations as for those receiving immediate therapy Consider S aureus and Pseudomonas infection for chronic otitis media"                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                , "Haemophilus influenzae Infections, p 400 Moraxella catarrhalis Infections, p 604 Streptococcus pneumoniae (P